# rule.require.repeatable-for-llm-tests

LLM tests must use `when.repeatably(REPEATABLE_CONFIG)` instead of plain `when`.

## config

```ts
const REPEATABLE_CONFIG = { attempts: 3, criteria: process.env.CI ? 'SOME' : 'EVERY' } as const;
```

| criteria | semantics |
|----------|-----------|
| `'SOME'` | pass if ANY attempt succeeds (CI) |
| `'EVERY'` | pass if ALL attempts succeed (local) |

## when to apply

- invokes brain, review, reflect operations
- calls any LLM internally

## when NOT to apply

- tests error conditions before LLM invocation
- tests pure/deterministic logic

## enforcement

LLM test without `when.repeatably` = **BLOCKER**
